{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/doc/guidelines/node-basics","result":{"data":{"page":{"name":"Node Basics","createdTime":"2021-04-26T14:38:31.456Z","modifiedTime":"11 days ago","breadcrumb":[{"name":"doc","slug":"/doc"},{"name":"guidelines","slug":"/doc/guidelines"},{"name":"Node Basics","slug":"/doc/guidelines/node-basics"}],"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"span-stylefont-size173emnode-basicsspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size173emnode-basicsspan\" aria-label=\"span stylefont size173emnode basicsspan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><span style='font-size:1.73em'>Node Basics</span></h2>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Basic Guideline for the use of Node.js as frontend development tool in context of Digital Editions.</span></p>\n<h3 id=\"prerequisites\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\" aria-label=\"prerequisites permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites</h3>\n<h5 id=\"span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insinstallation-requirementsinsspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insinstallation-requirementsinsspan\" aria-label=\"span stylefont size091emcolorrgb33 37 41insinstallation requirementsinsspan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Installation Requirements</ins></span></h5>\n<ol>\n<li><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>There are no required dependencies for the use of node.js</span></li>\n<li><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Recommended is to install VSCode to work with node.js</span></li>\n<li><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>In this Guideline node.js is described as frontend-development tool (compiling js / scss etc.) and not as Backend related technology. (Setting up http API)</span></li>\n</ol>\n<h5 id=\"span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41inssetupinsspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41inssetupinsspan\" aria-label=\"span stylefont size091emcolorrgb33 37 41inssetupinsspan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Setup</ins></span></h5>\n<ol>\n<li><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Install Node.js LTS version 12.x on your machine. (Googling node LTS should do the trick) With 12.x you should be able to run all ZIM related frontend code. Use higher versions at your own risk.</span></li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"quickstart\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#quickstart\" aria-label=\"quickstart permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Quickstart</h3>\n<h5 id=\"span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insdemoinsspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insdemoinsspan\" aria-label=\"span stylefont size091emcolorrgb33 37 41insdemoinsspan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Demo</ins></span></h5>\n<ol>\n<li><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Take a look at the React template in gitlab or the Docu Client itself.</span></li>\n<li><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Clone one of these repos and run \"npm i\" --- npm will then install all required dependencies from npmjs (=registry)</span></li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"cheatsheet\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cheatsheet\" aria-label=\"cheatsheet permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cheatsheet</h3>\n<h5 id=\"span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41inscommon-conceptsinsspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41inscommon-conceptsinsspan\" aria-label=\"span stylefont size091emcolorrgb33 37 41inscommon conceptsinsspan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Common concepts</ins></span></h5>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>#</strong></span></th>\n<th><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>Name</strong></span></th>\n<th><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>Related Keywords</strong></span></th>\n<th><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>Description</strong></span></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>1</strong></span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Node.js</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Chrome v8 Engine, Node</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Node is a runtime environment for executing JS code. Essentially, Node is a C++ program that embeds Chrome’s v8 engine, the fastest JS engine in the world. With Node you can build fast and scalable networking applications. It’s a common choice for building RESTful services. BUT: It also established itself as somewhat standard development tool for frontend-technologies.</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>2</strong></span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>NPM</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Node Package Manager, Dependency Management</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Npm allows to install, update, version etc. dependencies via the package.json. It therefor provides transparency which dependencies are used in which version in given code repo. Npm is the world's largest Software Registry. npm is installed with Node.js.</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>3</strong></span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>npmjs.com</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>NPM Registry, download dependencies.</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Web platform of npm that centralizes the exchange and reuse of code among Fronted Developers.</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><strong>4</strong></span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>package.json</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>dependency management</span></td>\n<td><span style='font-size:0.82em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>File in the root of every npm-node repository. Clarifies which dependencies (in which version) are needed to make the application run on the current machine.</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h5 id=\"span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insfrequently-needed-cli-commandsinsspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insfrequently-needed-cli-commandsinsspan\" aria-label=\"span stylefont size091emcolorrgb33 37 41insfrequently needed cli commandsinsspan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Frequently needed CLI Commands</ins></span></h5>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm i</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Install all dependencies stated in the package.json</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm i <packageName></span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Install a single dependency from npmjs (registry)</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm i <packageName><version></span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Install a single dependecy at specified version-number</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm i <packageName> --save-dev</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Install a single dependecy as development dependency</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm un <packageName></span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Uninstall a single dependecy.</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm outdated</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>View outdated dependencies according to package.json</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(12, 84, 96)'>npm update</span></p>\n<p><span style='color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'>Update dependencies</span></p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size173emnode-basicsspan\"><span style='font-size:1.73em'>Node Basics</span></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#prerequisites\">Prerequisites</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insinstallation-requirementsinsspan\"><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Installation Requirements</ins></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41inssetupinsspan\"><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Setup</ins></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#quickstart\">Quickstart</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insdemoinsspan\"><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Demo</ins></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#cheatsheet\">Cheatsheet</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41inscommon-conceptsinsspan\"><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Common concepts</ins></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#span-stylefont-size091emcolorrgb33-37-41insfrequently-needed-cli-commandsinsspan\"><span style='font-size:0.91em;color:rgb(33, 37, 41)'><ins>Frequently needed CLI Commands</ins></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"},"id":"1ZMPw6ExmQimBDyFCTiq_9SudUvKLYc6gUutgfluNsPU"}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["1215484441"]}